The paper proposes a motion-planning algorithm for robotic exploration and environmental monitoring, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm also involves information-theoretic convergence criterion, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of cameras for environmental monitoring, indicating the possibility of computer vision (cs.CV) being involved. Finally, the algorithm involves sampling-based techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
